text: The Withers House in Somerset, Kentucky, at 116 Maple St., was built in 1890. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1984. It was described in 1984 as one of Somerset's "largest and best preserved Queen Anne style homes." It is or was a two-story brick house with a one-story frame porch having Tuscan columns upon brick piers, and having a corner octagonal tower. With Photo of site The house may have been moved or destroyed. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Pulaski County, Kentucky Category:Queen Anne architecture in Kentucky Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1890
